raded as nyse it sp  component industry research founded   years ago  by gideon gartner headquarters stamford connecticut usa key people gene hall ceo craig safian cfo mike diliberto cio products research consulting events revenue us billion  operating income us million  net income us million  total assets us billion  total equity us million  number of employees   website gartnercom gartner inc is an american research and advisory firm providing information technology related insight for it and other business leaders located across the world its headquarters are in stamford connecticut united states it was known as gartner group inc until  when it was then changed to gartner research provided by gartner targets cios senior it marketing and supply chain leaders gartner clients include large corporations government agencies technology companies and the investment community the company consists of research executive programs consulting and events founded in  gartner has over  employees including  in research located in  countries gartner uses hype cycles and magic quadrants for visualization of its market analysis results contents  history  controversy  see also  references  external links historyedit the company was founded in  by gideon gartner originally a private company the gartner group was launched publicly the first time in the s then acquired by saatchi  saatchi a londonbased advertising agency and then acquired in  by some of its executives with funding from bain capital and dun  bradstreet the company went public again in  in  the name was simplified to gartner gene hall has been the ceo of the company since august  in the course of its growth gartner has acquired numerous companies providing related services including real decisions—which became gartner measurement now part of gartners consulting division—and gartner dataquest a market research firm it has also acquired a number of direct competitors including newscience in the late s meta group in  amr research and burton group in early  and ideas international in  in march  gartner announced that it had acquired the privately held company software advice for an undisclosed amount in july  gartner acquired nubera the business app discovery network that owns properties like getapp appstorm appappeal or cloudwork terms of the deal were not disclosed in september  it acquired the privately held company capterra in june  gartner announced that it had acquired the privately held company scm world headquartered in london uk on january   gartner announced it had reached an agreement to acquire ceb inc in a cash and stock deal worth about us billion controversyedit gartner has had a major controversy in forecasts in  gartner predicted the pc market would experience the sharpest unit decline in history and a few quarters later it reported strongest growth rate in seven years the actual shipment decline started the year  reaching peak decline in  see alsoedit connecticut portal companies portal information technology portal soundview technology group formerly gartner securities corp referencesedit  httpmarketsftcomdataequitiestearsheetfinancialssitnyqsubviewbalancesheet  httpmarketsftcomdataequitiestearsheetfinancialssitnyqsubviewbalancesheet  httpmarketsftcomdataequitiestearsheetfinancialssitnyqsubviewbalancesheet  httpmarketsftcomdataequitiestearsheetfinancialssitnyqsubviewbalancesheet  httpmarketsftcomdataequitiestearsheetfinancialssitnyqsubviewbalancesheet  edgar form q txt securities and exchange commission february     httpwwwgartnercomimagesrvpdfgartnercorpfactsheetgartnerataglancepdf  gartner corp fact sheet pdf   about gartner retrieved march     gartner group records  finding aid university of minnesota   gartner group inc history fundinguniverse retrieved    gartner copyright  quote policy  section  attribution wwwgartnercom  retrieved    gartner acquires software advice gartnercom gartner inc  retrieved    novoa jaime  gartner acquires barcelonabased nubera getapp 