er originally a private company the gartner group was launched publicly the first time in the s then acquired by saatchi  saatchi a londonbased advertising agency and then acquired in  by some of its executives with funding from bain capital and dun  bradstreet the company went public again in  in  the name was simplified to gartner gene hall has been the ceo of the company since august  in the course of its growth gartner has acquired numerous companies providing related services including real decisions—which became gartner measurement now part of gartners consulting division—and gartner dataquest a market research firm it has also acquired a number of direct competitors including newscience in the late s meta group in  amr research and burton group in early  and ideas international in  in march  gartner announced that it had acquired the privately held company software advice for an undisclosed amount in july  gartner acquired nubera the business app discovery network that owns properties like getapp appstorm appappeal or cloudwork terms of the deal were not disclosed in september  it acquired the privately held company capterra in june  gartner announced that it had acquired the privately held company scm world headquartered in london uk on january   gartner announced it had reached an agreement to acquire ceb inc in a cash and stock deal worth about us billion controversyedit gartner has had a major controversy in forecasts in  gartner predicted the pc market would experience the sharpest unit decline in history and a few quarters later it reported strongest growth rate in seven years the actual shipment decline started the year  reaching peak decline in  see alsoedit connecticut portal companies portal information technology portal soundview technology group formerly gartner securities corp referencesedit  httpmarketsftcomdataequitiestearsheetfinancialssitnyqsubviewbalancesheet  httpmarketsftcomdataequitiestearsheetfinancialssitnyqsubviewbalancesheet  httpmark